quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  27,15,"And We gave David and Solomon knowledge and they said, 'Praise belongs to God who has preferred us over many of His believing servants"
  27,16,"And Solomon was David's heir, and he said, 'Men, we have been taught the speech of the birds, and we have been given of everything; surely this is indeed the manifest bounty"
  27,17,"And his hosts were mustered to Solomon, jinn, men and birds, duly disposed"
  27,18,"till, when they came on the Valley of Ants, an ant said, 'Ants, enter your dwelling-places, lest Solomon and his hosts crush you, being unaware"
  27,19,"But he smiled, laughing at its words, and he said, 'My Lord, dispose me that I may be thankful for Thy blessing wherewith Thou hast blessed me and my father and mother, and that I may do righteousness well-pleasing to Thee; and do Thou admit me, by Thy mercy, amongst Thy righteous servants"
  27,20,"And he reviewed the birds; then he said, 'How is it with me, that I do not see the hoopoe? Or is he among the absent"
  27,21,"Assuredly I will chastise him with a terrible chastisement, or I will slaughter him, or he bring me a clear authority"
  27,22,"But he tarried not long, and said, 'I have comprehended that which thou hast not comprehended, and I have come from Sheba to thee with a sure tiding"
  27,23,"I found a woman ruling over them, and she has been given of everything, and she possesses a mighty throne"
  27,24,"I found her and her people prostrating to the sun, apart from God; Satan has decked out fair their deeds to them and he has barred them from the way, and therefore they are not guided"
  27,25,"so that they prostrate not themselves to God, who brings forth what is hidden in the heavens and earth; and He knows what you conceal and what you publish"
  27,26,"God: there is no god but He, the Lord of the Mighty Throne"
  27,27,"Said he, 'Now We will see whether thou hast spoken truly, or whether thou art amongst those that lie"
  27,28,"Take this letter of mine, and cast it unto them, then turn back from them and see what they shall return"
  27,29,"She said, 'O Council, see, a letter honourable has been cast unto me"
  27,30,"It is from Solomon, and it is \"In the Name of God, the Merciful, the Compassionate"
  27,31,"Rise not up against me, but come to me in surrender"